<h2>The Hamptons Architecture</h2>
<p>The Hamptons provides a wealth of real estate options to accommodate your every need and preference. Constructed largely in the mid-2000s, the modern real estate in The Hamptons was established by such esteemed developers as Chancellor, Goldmark, Westglen, Calbridge, Sundance, Janssen, Lupi, Classic Craft, Glenwood, and Beattie.</p>
<p>Complete with ever-present sophistication, most homes for sale in The Hamptons proudly blend a traditional appearance with modern design choices. Substantial single-family homes with 2-story floor plans are the norm in The Hamptons, but smaller ranch or villa-style homes are also plentiful.</p>
<p>The ever-popular La Vita Complex is characterized by a series of bungalow style villas and townhomes, complete with attached garages and ample interior amenities. The Chateaux One is a suitable choice for the frequent golfer, as it backs directly onto the number one hole of the Hamptons Golf Course.</p>
</div>
</div>
